    <div id="fontsize">
    <p id="paragraph1"> Artificial Intelligence, according to <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artificial_intelligence"> this Wikipedia article </a> is:
    <br>
    <br>
    <b> Intelligence demonstrated by machines, in contrast to the natural intelligence displayed by humans and other animals. </b></p>
    
     <p id="paragraph2">
       Artificial Intelligence is basically just a program that demonstrates similar intelligence to that of a human or animal. 
       These systems are very huge, complex strings and files of code. 
       Basic AI can be conditional statements.
     </p>
     <p id="paragraph3">
       These conditional statements can be written in various languages. They can be written in JavaScript, Python, pretty much any language that can stand by itself.
     </p>
     <p id="paragraph4">
       You can't write a (very, very, very, very BASIC) AI program in HTML alone, since it is a markup language that has to work with CSS and JavaScript
     </p>
